class Solution {
    public boolean makeStringsEqual(String s, String target) {
        boolean hasOneS = false;
        boolean hasOneTarget = false;
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == '1') hasOneS = true;
            if (target.charAt(i) == '1') hasOneTarget = true;
        }
        return hasOneS == hasOneTarget;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The key observation is that the operation can create a '1' if at least one '1' exists, but cannot eliminate all '1's if any exist. Thus, s can reach target iff both strings contain at least one '1' or both contain none.

